1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,950
There is a house in New Orleans

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:13,950
They call the Rising Sun

3
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:22,950
It's been the ruin of many a poor girl

4
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:45,950
And me, oh Lord, I'm one

5
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:56,950
If I had listened to what my mother said

6
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:06,950
I'd have been at home today

7
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:19,950
But I was young and foolish, oh God

8
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:26,950
Let a rambler lead me astray

9
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:35,950
My mother was a tailor

10
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:47,950
She sewed my new blue jeans

11
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:59,950
My sweetheart was a gambling man

12
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:06,950
Down in New Orleans

13
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:16,950
Oh mothers, tell your children

14
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:28,950
Not to do what I have done

15
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:38,950
To spend their lives in sin and misery

16
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:51,950
In the house of the Rising Sun

17
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:59,950
I'm going back to New Orleans

18
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:12,950
My race is almost run

19
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:23,950
I'm going back to spend my life

20
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:28,000
Beneath the Rising Sun
